            2023</ref>)</sourceNote><commencementNote>[27 June 2001]</commencementNote><sourceNote>(Format changes—<ref href="/hk/2023/er3">E.R. 3 of 2023</ref>)</sourceNote><section id="ID_1438402768981_001" name="s1" reason="omittedAsSpent" startPeriod="2023-10-12" status="omitted" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><sourceNote>(Omitted as spent—<ref href="/hk/2023/er3">E.R. 3 of 2023</ref>)</sourceNote></section><section id="ID_1438402768981_003" name="s2" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2001-06-27" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Collar for fighting dogs and known dangerous dogs</heading><content>The keeper of a fighting dog or a known dangerous dog shall ensure that the dog is identified at all times by wearing a collar which conforms to the specifications specified in the <ref>Schedule</ref>.</content></section><schedule id="ID_1438402768997_001" name="sch0" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2023-10-12" status="operational" temporalId="sch0"><num value="0">Schedule</num><note class="align_right" role="crossReferences" type="inline">[<ref href="/hk/cap167E/s2">s. 2</ref>]</note><heading>Specifications
                                    of Collar for Fighting Dog or Known Dangerous
                                    Dog<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></heading><text>The collar must be at least 1.5 cm wide marked on its obverse side
                                    with a bright yellow background and at least 4 red diagonal
                                    stripes. The stripes must be at least 1.5 cm apart and each of
                                    them must be at least 1.5 cm wide.</text></schedule></main></subLeg>